value: Bought in the bazaar of Constantinople, March 1924

Porcelain baluster vase, divided by grooves into six sections, each decorated with panels containing birds and flowers. There are six panels of clouds on the shoulder.  On the neck are another six panels, of plants.  All painted in blue under the glaze, on a white ground.

summary_title: Chinese Ornament: The Lotus and the Dragon
Oriental Blue and White (Monographs on Pottery and Porcelain)
